At the time of the 2010 Census, Stacy had a population of 1,456 people. This makes Stacy the county's 6th most populous community. The population of Stacy represents 0.03% of the population of Minnesota (which has 5,303,925 people), making it the state's 297th most populous community. With a 2010 count of 1,456 people, the population of Stacy increased 13.93% from the 2000 Census (which had a count of 1,278 people).

Stacy is located in southeast Minnesota. Stacy is between the Chisago, Washington, Anoka, Isanti county. Stacy has 3.51 square miles of land area and 0.07 square miles of water area. As of 2010-2014, the total Stacy population is 1,539, which has grown 20.42% since 2000. The population growth rate is much higher than the state average rate of 9.44% and is much higher than the national average rate of 11.61%.
